<br>
Skalds while not the uber class of all Vahalla that all non-skalds try to make us out to be, are good.  Lets state that right off.  No need to be discouraged.  Yes there are problems but we are better than many classes (and worse than many, but hey, thats ok).  Let me just say if you got into skald thinking you are a major damage dealer or tank class, re-roll.  You can be but not without many RAs.<br>
<br>
Thats out of the way.<br>
<br>
If you plan to solo alot, I wouldnt go axe.  Axe has some of the best styles you'll get in midgard but endurance is an issue for skalds.  This is because our instas (dds, mez, snare, DA, basically everything) cost power AND endurance.  A solo skald, IMHO, should seriously consider hammer.  Decent damge and decent styles.  The level 15 hammer style Provoke uses minimal endurance.  Thats not to say axe is out but it eats endurance fast.  Of course, endurance regenerates fast but I think hammer is better solo, axe better groupage.<br>
<br>
Spec?  Well, thats up for debate.  Many good templates out there, including:<br>
50 weapon/43 Battlesongs/2 Parry<br>
47weapon/46 battle songs/5 Parry<br>
46/46/10<br>
44/46/17<br>
There are others but, IMHO, these are the best choices.  i prefer 44/46/17 (known as the cookie cutter spec) because of its versatility, and skalds are all about versability.  Many will say 17 parry is a waste, and sometimes thats true, but with +11 items and an average of +4-5 from Realm Rank and MoParry, its not too bad.  Plus, if you're like me and enjoy PvE as much as RvR its helpful to have decent parry.  <br>
<br>
The one thing ALL skalds will agree on is that you must have AT LEAST 43 in battlesongs for the highest speed chant.  All group want at least one skald for the speed, so you need the highest one.  Also ALL skalds will agree you should never go 45 in battle songs.  Pick either 43 (for highest speed) or 46 (for best damage add).  Then put weapon to a high level with remainder in parry.   <p>Albron<br>
Level 50 Norse Skald<br>
HOOKED on speed!<br>
